          <p style="font-size: 12px; line-height: 1.2; color: #A9A7AF;"><i>US Middle East envoy Steve Witkoff in Riyadh, Saudi Arabia. Credits: Evelyn Hockstein/POOL/AFP via Getty Images
          </i></p>
        </mj-text> 

        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
         
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">Donald Trump’s special envoy, Steve Witkoff, dismissed UK Prime Minister Keir Starmer’s proposal for an international force to <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-24-03-2025-h1-1-support-a-ukraine-ceasefire?source=website" target="_blank">support a Ukraine ceasefire</a>, calling it “a posture and a pose” and “simplistic.” Witkoff heckled European leaders for trying to act like Winston Churchill and said they exaggerated the Russian threat. After meeting Putin recently, Witkoff praised him, calling him “super smart.”</p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5; filter:blur(5px);">He claimed Putin prayed for Trump after last year’s assassination attempt and gifted him a portrait. Witkoff called Ukraine “a false country” and suggested Russia rightfully controls five regions.  He also cited their support for Russia in referendums, although they were later discredited. Witkoff also claims that Ukraine has agreed to hold presidential elections and largely accepts not joining NATO. 
       </p>
        </mj-text>
